One limitation on Shopify Audiences is that it is only available to retaile=
rs with a Shopify Plus subscription, which costs $2,000/month, and from my =
perspective is a big reason to subscribe to that very high margin product. =
Eric Seufert, however, argues that this is a mistake; from MobileDevMemo ( =
https://mobiledevmemo.com/the-necessity-of-shopify-audiences/ ) :

Shopify likely can=E2=80=99t launch an ad network, given the nature of its =
relationship with retailers. But it did the next best thing by creating an =
audience network: monetizing the data it owns by empowering retailers to fi=
nd and advertise to known, relevant customers. While Shopify doesn=E2=80=99=
t charge retailers for use of its Audience product, since it=E2=80=99s incl=
uded with the Shopify Plus subscription, the company benefits when its reta=
ilers are able to efficiently target new customers and drive incremental sa=
les=E2=80=A6

Shopify can drive topline growth without attendant increases to its cost ba=
se by aggressively expanding its Audience Network: not only to new platform=
s but to more retailers within its network, possibly by making the product =
available to merchants outside of its Plus platform. I=E2=80=99d argue that=
 Audiences likely isn=E2=80=99t a compelling enticement to SMBs to upgrade =
their Shopify merchant stores to Shopify Plus: with advertising performance=
, seeing is believing, and an SMB can=E2=80=99t know what effect Shopify Au=
diences will have on their business a priori to justify the $2,000 monthly =
expense. Similarly, counterfactuals related to advertising performance can =
also be unconvincing (eg. =E2=80=9CYou would have generated 30% more sales =
last month had you used our advertising technology=E2=80=9D).

Expanding Audiences to all retailers could potentially grow GMV and revenue=
 by activating more incremental sales, arguably without cannibalizing Shopi=
fy Plus recurring revenue. There are obviously other considerations, and Sh=
opify hasn=E2=80=99t fully made public the details of the Audience Network =
(ie. which and whose data is input into Audience segments), but the opportu=
nity seems attractive.

This is an articulation of the elasticity point I made above: from my persp=
ective Shopify Audiences is probably the single most compelling reason to s=
ubscribe to Shopify Plus, if not now then in the future as Shopify ramps it=
 up. There simply isn=E2=80=99t anything more valuable in terms of online c=
ommerce than better targeted advertising. Seufert=E2=80=99s argument, thoug=
h, is that small merchants can=E2=80=99t and won=E2=80=99t appreciate the v=
alue, particularly given how daunting that $2,000/month price point is; wor=
se, because such a huge portion of Shopify=E2=80=99s merchant base is not a=
 part of the program, Shopify Audiences has less data and thus generates le=
ss value. Therefore Shopify ought to make Shopify Audiences available to ev=
eryone.

The problem for Shopify is that weakening the attractiveness of Shopify Plu=
s in the pursuit of increased gross merchant volume would have a huge effec=
t on margins; consider some back of the envelope math for a single merchant=
:

* $2,000/month at 79% gross margin for Subscription Solutions is $1,580 in =
gross profit.
* $1,580 in gross profit from Merchant Solutions, which has 30% gross margi=
ns, requires $5,267 in revenue.
* Most Merchant Solutions revenue comes from payment processing and currenc=
y conversions, and Shopify Payments fees for Shopify Plus accounts are 2.4%=
 + $0.30; that means the merchant needs somewhere around $200,000 in gross =
merchant volume to generate $5,267 in Merchant Solutions revenue for Shopif=
y.

Now obviously Shopify would benefit from increased merchant volume not just=
 amongst Shopify Plus merchants but also all of the smaller merchants who c=
an now dip their toe into ads. It=E2=80=99s a huge amount of gross profit t=
o make up, though, and a good example of the tension Shopify is surely feel=
ing as Subscription Solutions revenue growth falters.

