ons using the app every month, we=E2=80=99re able to match the right mercha=
nts to the right buyers, creating personalized shopping feeds for the buyer=
 segment and a new customer acquisition tool for merchants. Shop is still i=
n its early days, but it=E2=80=99s one of the ways we=E2=80=99re investing =
to help merchants win over the long-term.

I=E2=80=99m less hostile to the concept of the Shop App than I was at first=
, although I do think that Shop Minis should be a precursor to a new SDK th=
at can be placed in any app, not just the Shop App.

Ultimately, though, the reason I am less hostile is because Shopify is in a=
 new environment: all of this stuff, from building a consumer-facing Aggreg=
ator to an Audience Network is hard, both for Shopify and for merchants. Fo=
r the former there is no choice given the reality of the post ATT world, wh=
ere it=E2=80=99s no longer viable to offload the hard work of customer acqu=
isition and Aggregation to Facebook; for the latter there is that much high=
er of a barrier to get started, which is a reminder that saturation, to the=
 extent it is occurring, is not just a function of reaching an addressable =
market, but of that addressable market shrinking thanks to secular changes =
of the sort caused by ATT.

